Text: '
"'''America the Beautiful'''" is an '
Reference: United States 'American'
Text: ' '
Reference: patriotic song ''
Text: '. The lyrics were written by '
Reference: Katharine Lee Bates ''
Text: ' and the music composed by church organist and choirmaster '
Reference: Samuel A. Ward ''
Text: '.

Bates originally wrote the words as a poem, ''Pikes Peak'', first published in the '
Reference: Fourth of July ''
Text: ' edition of the church periodical ''The Congregationalist'' in 1895. At that time, the poem was titled ''America'' for publication.

Ward had originally written the music, ''Materna'', for the hymn '''
Reference: O Mother dear, Jerusalem ''
Text: ''' in 1882. Ward's music combined with the Bates poem was first published in 1910 and titled ''America the Beautiful''.

The song is one of the most beloved and popular of the many American patriotic songs.'
