Section [0] Idioms
Text: '
'''"From sea to shining sea"''' is an '
Reference: United States 'American'
Text: ' '
Reference: idiom ''
Text: ' meaning from the '
Reference: Atlantic Ocean ''
Text: ' to the '
Reference: Pacific Ocean ''
Text: ' (or vice versa).  Many songs have used this term, including the American patriotic songs "America, The Beautiful" and "'
Reference: God Bless the USA ''
Text: '".  In addition to these, it is also featured in '
Reference: Schoolhouse Rock ''
Text: ''s "Elbow Room".  A term similar to this is the '
Reference: Canada 'Canadian'
Text: ' motto '''
Reference: A Mari Usque Ad Mare ''
Text: ''' ("From sea to sea.")

